When resolving a conflict on an **Delete-Update** situation (where **Update** should win), the **Update** is not applied, since row does not exist anymore

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4592555/71449804-56c9f180-2755-11ea-81c5-a4b82aa833c0.png)

The reason is the **Update stored procedure**, which does not try to insert the row, if the row does not exist:

``` sql
ALTER PROCEDURE [dbo].[ProductCategory_update]
	@ProductCategoryID int,
	@ParentProductCategoryID int,
	@Name nvarchar(50),
	@rowguid uniqueidentifier,
	@ModifiedDate datetime,
	@sync_force_write int,
	@sync_min_timestamp bigint,
	@sync_row_count int OUTPUT
AS
BEGIN
SET @sync_row_count = 0;

UPDATE [ProductCategory]
SET  [ParentProductCategoryID] = @ParentProductCategoryID
,  [Name] = @Name
,  [rowguid] = @rowguid
,  [ModifiedDate] = @ModifiedDate
FROM [ProductCategory] [base]
JOIN [ProductCategory_tracking] [side]
ON [base].[ProductCategoryID] = [side].[ProductCategoryID]
WHERE ([side].[timestamp] <= @sync_min_timestamp OR @sync_force_write = 1)
AND ([base].[ProductCategoryID] = @ProductCategoryID);

SET @sync_row_count = @@ROWCOUNT;
END
```
One possible solution should be to try to insert the row, if the row exist in the tracking table and not in the original table:

``` sql
ALTER PROCEDURE [dbo].[ProductCategory_update]
	@[bla bla bla]
AS
BEGIN
SET @sync_row_count = 0;

UPDATE [ProductCategory]
SET ... [bla bla bla]

-- try to Insert row if not exists in the original table
SET IDENTITY_INSERT [ProductCategory] ON;

INSERT INTO [ProductCategory]
([ProductCategoryID], [ParentProductCategoryID], [Name], [rowguid], [ModifiedDate])
SELECT @ProductCategoryID, @ParentProductCategoryID, @Name, @rowguid, @ModifiedDate
FROM [ProductCategory] [base]
RIGHT JOIN [ProductCategory_tracking] [side]
ON [base].[ProductCategoryID] = [side].[ProductCategoryID]
WHERE ([side].[timestamp] <= @sync_min_timestamp OR [side].[update_scope_id] is not null OR @sync_force_write = 1)
AND ([base].[ProductCategoryID] IS NULL AND [side].[ProductCategoryID] = @ProductCategoryID);


SET IDENTITY_INSERT [ProductCategory] OFF;

SET @sync_row_count = @@ROWCOUNT;
END
```

